Here are the public test cases for feature5_1_host_function_args:
{
  "description": "A module function that calls back into a host-provided function; the host import records the arguments it receives, demonstrating values flow from module code into the host callback.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "module": "0061736d0100000001090260027e7e00600000020e0103656e76067265706f72740000030201010405017001010105030100020608017f01418088040b071802066d656d6f727902000b7265706f7274537475666600010a10010e0042fb0042c8031080808080000b",
        "imports": [
          {
            "kind": "function",
            "module": "env",
            "name": "report",
            "behavior": "echo_args",
            "arity": 2
          }
        ],
        "build": true,
        "steps": [
          {
            "op": "invoke",
            "name": "reportStuff",
            "args": []
          },
          {
            "op": "import_call",
            "ref": "env::report"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "result[reportStuff]=void\nimport_call[env::report]=123,456\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the public test cases for feature5_2_host_function_exception:
{
  "description": "When a host-provided import raises an error during a module call, the error propagates out of the call and is reported with a normalized category plus the error message.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "module": "0061736d0100000001040160000002110203656e760161000003656e7601620000030201000405017001010105030100020608017f01418088040b070f02066d656d6f7279020002666e00020a10010e001080808080001081808080000b",
        "imports": [
          {
            "kind": "function",
            "module": "env",
            "name": "a",
            "behavior": "throw",
            "message": "Hello exception!",
            "arity": 0
          },
          {
            "kind": "function",
            "module": "env",
            "name": "b",
            "behavior": "return",
            "arity": 0,
            "value": null
          }
        ],
        "build": true,
        "steps": [
          {
